From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000023 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@local>
Date: Wed, 15 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] KVM: Force old-ABI private normal-slot mappings to 4K

Patch 0017 disables only cofunc_tdx_oldabi_private_2m_capable(), the custom
4K-to-2M promotion helper.  It does not prevent
__kvm_mmu_max_mapping_level() from selecting a 2M mapping when the normal
host HVA walk sees a THP-backed PMD.

That distinction matters for the Vanilla Kata-TDX containment A/B.  A run
with patch 0017 still logged a live private level-2 split.  Two preserved
failures show KVM operating on 4K children while the TDX module encounters
a blocked level-1 SEPT ancestor.  Therefore the earlier run was not a true
4K-only test.

For old-ABI TDX private faults backed by a normal memslot, cap the normal
KVM mapping decision at PG_LEVEL_4K and return before the custom promotion
helper.  Log cases where the ordinary KVM decision would have installed a
larger mapping.  Shared mappings and private-capable memslots keep their
normal KVM policy.

This is a conservative Vanilla Kata containment diagnostic.  It is not a
fix for the underlying SEPT split-state bug.  It also disables the CoFunc
private 2M optimization, so CoFunc measurements must not be collected with
this module.

Signed-off-by: Codex <codex@local>
---
 arch/x86/kvm/mmu/mmu.c | 20 ++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 20 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/x86/kvm/mmu/mmu.c b/arch/x86/kvm/mmu/mmu.c
--- a/arch/x86/kvm/mmu/mmu.c
+++ b/arch/x86/kvm/mmu/mmu.c
@@ -3267,6 +3267,7 @@ out:
 }
 
 static atomic_t cofunc_tdx_oldabi_private_2m_log_budget = ATOMIC_INIT(64);
+static atomic_t cofunc_tdx_oldabi_private_4k_log_budget = ATOMIC_INIT(64);
 static atomic_t cofunc_tdx_oldabi_private_2m_disabled_log_budget = ATOMIC_INIT(64);
 
 static unsigned long cofunc_tdx_oldabi_lpage_disallow(gfn_t gfn,
@@ -3400,6 +3401,25 @@ void kvm_mmu_hugepage_adjust(struct kvm_vcpu *vcpu, struct kvm_page_fault *fault)
 	fault->req_level = __kvm_mmu_max_mapping_level(vcpu->kvm, slot,
 						       fault->gfn, fault->max_level,
 						       fault->host_level);
+
+	/*
+	 * Vanilla old-ABI TDX containment: normal host THP policy must not
+	 * silently restore private 2M mappings after the custom promotion
+	 * helper has been disabled.
+	 */
+	if (fault->is_private && slot && !kvm_slot_can_be_private(slot)) {
+		if (fault->req_level > PG_LEVEL_4K &&
+		    atomic_dec_if_positive(&cofunc_tdx_oldabi_private_4k_log_budget) >= 0)
+			pr_info("CoFunc old-ABI private mapping forced to 4K: gfn=0x%llx pfn=0x%llx normal_req=%u capped_req=%u max=%u host=%u slot_flags=0x%lx hva=0x%lx\n",
+				(unsigned long long)fault->gfn,
+				(unsigned long long)fault->pfn,
+				fault->req_level, PG_LEVEL_4K, fault->max_level,
+				fault->host_level, (unsigned long)slot->flags,
+				(unsigned long)fault->hva);
+		fault->req_level = PG_LEVEL_4K;
+		return;
+	}
+
 	old_req_level = fault->req_level;
 	if (cofunc_tdx_oldabi_private_2m_capable(fault, &pfn_order)) {
 		fault->req_level = PG_LEVEL_2M;
-- 
